-- Deals of the day- Mergers and acquisitions
-- 
-- Wed Sep 03, 2014 06:20AM EDT
-- None



Sept 3 (Reuters) - The following bids, mergers, acquisitions and disposals were reported by 1020 GMT on Wednesday:

** Private equity firms Carlyle Group LP <CG.O> and Fountainvest Partners have pulled out of a consortium backing a $1.9 billion bid to buy U.S. listed online games developer Shanda Games Ltd <GAME.O>, Shanda said on Wednesday. [ID:nL3N0R42A8]  ** Buckeye Partners LP <BPL.N> said it would pay $860 million for 80 percent of Trafigura AG's [TRAFGF.UL] membership interests in certain midstream assets linking South Texas to the Gulf Coast. [ID:nL3N0R34Z7]  ** United Internet AG <UTDI.DE> agreed on Wednesday to buy KKR & Co LP's <KKR.N> stake in cable group Versatel for about 586 million euros ($769 million) in cash, giving it access to Germany's second-largest fibre optic cable network. [ID:nL5N0R411P]  ** Colombia's Cabinet has authorized state-run oil company Ecotpetrol SA <ECO.CN> to sell its 1.1 trillion peso ($573 million) stake in energy generator Empresa Energia de Bogota SA ESP <EEB.CN>, the company said in a statement on Tuesday. [ID:nL1N0R323O]  ** Crescent Point Energy Corp <CPG.TO> said on Tuesday that it had reached a C$378 million ($346 million) deal to buy producing conventional oil assets in Saskatchewan and Manitoba, along with undeveloped land, from Lightstream Resources Ltd <LTS.TO>. [ID:nL1N0R32FY]  ** Metro AG <MEOG.DE> has sold its stake in Britain's biggest cash-and-carry wholesaler, Booker Group Plc <BOK.L>, for 196 million pounds ($323 million) as the German retailer looks to reinvest capital and trim debt. [ID:nL5N0R41JW]  ** Directors of Malaysia's BP Healthcare, a diagnostics-to-laboratory medical group, plan to raise up to 500 million ringgit ($157 million) through a special purpose acquisition vehicle (SPAC) listing next year, according to two sources with direct knowledge of the deal. [ID:nL3N0R41QT]  ** Poland's PKP Cargo, the European Union's No.2 rail cargo operator by tonnage transported, wants to buy its rival CTL Logistics to gain a stronger foothold in Poland and Germany, it said on Wednesday. [ID:nW8N0QK015]  ** Russia's Norilsk Nickel <GMKN.MM>, the world's largest nickel and palladium producer, said on Wednesday it had agreed to sell its Australian Lake Johnston project to Poseidon Nickel Ltd <POS.AX>. [ID:nL5N0R40TD]  ** Travel management and expense software maker Concur Technologies Inc <CNQR.O> is exploring a sale of the company and has approached Oracle Corp <ORCL.N> and Germany's SAP SE <SAPG.DE>, Bloomberg reported, citing people with knowledge of the matter. [ID:nL3N0R35C5]  ** German Economy Minister Sigmar Gabriel is in favor of a merger of defense firm Krauss-Maffei Wegmann with peer Rheinmetall AG <RHMG.DE>, German weekly newspaper Die Zeit reported on Wednesday. [ID:nWEA00F4W]  ** JPMorgan Chase & Co <JPM.N> is in talks to sell its oil-supply agreement with a major Philadelphia refinery to Bank of America Corp <BAC.N>, the Wall Street Journal reported Tuesday, citing people familiar with the matter. [ID:nL3N0R35NL]  ** Malaysia's Tanjung Langsat Port [JOHORL.UL] plans to sell its storage tank terminal in the southern state of Johor and has short-listed at least five companies for a second round of negotiations, sources close to the matter told Reuters. [ID:nL3N0R41QI]  ** French luxury groups LVMH <LVMH.PA> and Hermes International SCA <HRMS.PA> have settled their dispute over LVMH's 23.2 percent stake in the maker of Birkin and Kelly handbags, striking a deal under which the holding will be distributed among LVMH's shareholders. [ID:nL5N0R415Q]  ** Italy will go on with a plan to privatize state-owned companies, but its Prime Minister Matteo Renzi does not see as a priority the sale of stakes in energy companies Eni SpA <ENI.MI> and Enel SpA <ENEI.MI>, he told financial daily Il Sole 24 Ore. [ID:nL5N0R40GS]